723611f-a.title: Manhattan: Union Square (East) - 15th Street.
723611f-a.text:
I)nnion Square Savings Bank, Union Square East at N.E. corner of 15th
Street, with part of the newly remodelled park in the foreground.
This edifice was built some time between 1902 and 1910, replacing two
old houses; the bank had its original offices in 20 Union Sduare,
on the corner. The 9-story apartment house at 107 East 15th Street,
adjoining the bank, was built about 1900.
August 4, 1930.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.

723618f-a.title: Manhattan: Union Square (East) - 15th Street.
723618f-a.text:
Union Square East, north from and including 15th Street (Fourth
Ave, as shown is a continuation of Union Square East).
About 1913.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
